{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}} {{Infobox person | image = Américo Amorim 2009-12-29.png | image_size = | name = Américo Amorim | caption = Américo Amorim in 2009 | birth_name = Américo Ferreira Amorim | birth_date = {{Birth date|1934|7|21|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Mozelos (Santa Maria da Feira)|Mozelos]], [[Santa Maria da Feira Municipality|Santa Maria da Feira]], Portugal | death_date = {{Death date and age|2017|7|13|1934|7|21|df=y}} | death_place = [[Grijó (Vila Nova de Gaia)|Grijo]], Portugal | death_cause = | restingplace = | nationality = Portuguese | religion = | ethnicity = | residence = | education = | alma mater = | occupation = Heir, investor | known for = 50% interest in [[Corticeira Amorim]] | salary = | networth = [[United States dollar|$]]4.8 billion (July 2017)<ref name=Forbes>{{cite web|title=Americo Amorim|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/americo-amorim/|website=Forbes|accessdate=13 July 2017}}</ref> | spouse = | parents = | children = 3 | relatives = | website = }} '''Américo Ferreira Amorim''' (21 July 1934 – 13 July 2017) was a Portuguese industrialist and businessman. He was ranked by ''[[Forbes]]'' as the 385th richest person in the world in January 2015.<ref name=Forbes/>
==Early life== Amorim was born in [[Mozelos (Santa Maria da Feira)|Mozelos]] in 1934, the fifth of eight children of Américo Alves Amorim, into a "modest family".<ref name="abcnews1">{{cite web|author=barry hatton, associated press |url=http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/americo-amorim-thought-portugals-richest-man-dies-48614152 |title=Americo Amorim, thought to be Portugal's richest man, dies - ABC News |publisher=Abcnews.go.com |date= |accessdate=13 July 2017}}</ref>
==Career== He owned a 50% interest in [[Corticeira Amorim]], founded by his grandfather in 1870, and the world's largest producer of [[cork (material)|cork]], with $650 million in sales.<ref name=Forbes/> He also had interests in finance and energy.<ref name=Forbes/>
==Personal life== Américo Amorim was married to Maria Fernanda de Oliveira Ramos, the daughter of medical doctor Manuel Pinto Moreira Ramos and Maria José Nunes de Oliveira, and had three daughters.<ref>[http://www.geneall.net/P/per_page.php?id=476467 Américo Ferreira de Amorim] - GeneAll.net</ref> They lived in [[Grijó (Vila Nova de Gaia)|Grijó]].<ref name=Forbes/>
He died on 13 July 2017.<ref name="abcnews1"/>
