{{Infobox person | name = Khulubuse Zuma | known_for = implication in the [[Panama Papers]] leak | relatives = [[Jacob Zuma]] (uncle) | nationality = [[South Africa|South African]] | occupation = [[businessperson|Businessman]] | partner = Fikisiwe Dlamini }}
'''Clive Khulubuse Zuma''' is a South African businessman, and the nephew of the former [[President of South Africa|President]], [[Jacob Zuma]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Poplak|first1=Richard|title=Trainspotter: Panama Papers – How Zuma’s family is implicated in the greatest corruption data dump of all time|url=http://www.dailymaverick.co.za/article/2016-04-04-trainspotter-panama-papers-how-zumas-family-is-implicated-in-the-greatest-corruption-data-dump-of-all-time/#.VwOuT0m7qR0|website=Daily Maverick|accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Mthethwa|first1=Bongani|title=Khulubuse Zuma: Lapping up the good life|url=http://www.timeslive.co.za/local/2011/04/17/khulubuse-zuma-lapping-up-the-good-life|website=Time Live|publisher=Times Media Group|accessdate=17 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Khulubuse Zuma’s R100bn oil deal|url=http://www.news24.com/Archives/City-Press/Khulubuse-Zumas-R100bn-oil-deal-20150430-2|website=City Press|publisher=News22|accessdate=18 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Kimber|first1=Charlie|title=Corruption scandals hit Zuma in South Africa - and cause a crisis for the ANC|url=https://socialistworker.co.uk/art/42467/Corruption+scandals+hit+Zuma+in+South+Africa+-+and+cause+a+crisis+for+the+ANC|website=Socialist Worker|accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref>
Zuma was named in the [[Panama Papers]] leak as a result of his links to oilfields in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] (DRC). Shortly after [[Jacob Zuma|President Zuma]], his uncle, met with DRC president [[Joseph Kabila]], Zuma's company Caprikat Limited secured a R100 billion rand oil deal in the DRC.<ref name="n24">{{cite web | url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/the-panama-papers-and-the-zuma-link-20160404 | title=The Panama papers and the Zuma link | publisher=News24 | date=4 April 2016 | accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref>
In 2014, he got engaged to Swazi princess, Fikisiwe Dlamini.<ref>[http://you.co.za/news/this-is-what-its-like-to-have-lunch-at-nkandla/ This is what it’s like to have lunch at Nkandla] ''you.co.za''</ref>
