The '''Life Sciences Research Foundation''' ('''LSRF''') is a postdoctoral fellowship program, with missions "''to identify and fund exceptional young scientists at a critical juncture of their training in all areas of basic life sciences''" and "''to establish partnerships between those who support research in the life sciences and academic institutions for their mutual benefit''".<ref>{{cite web | accessdate=25 May 2013 | url = http://www.lsrf.org/ | title= Life Sciences Research Foundation}}</ref> LSRF was established in 1983 by [[Donald D. Brown]] of the Carnegie Institution for Science, Department of Embryology. As one of four highly competitive postdoctoral awards in the life sciences,<ref>{{cite web|title=''JCC Fund Newsletter'' |date=2007 |url=http://www.jccfund.org/sites/default/files/linked_content/JCCNews2007v9%20Final.pdf |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150210085223/http://www.jccfund.org/sites/default/files/linked_content/JCCNews2007v9%20Final.pdf |archivedate=2015-02-10 |df= }}</ref> each year LSRF receives more than 1000 applications and awards 15-25 fellowships. The Board of Directors also includes [[Douglas Koshland]] and [[Solomon H. Snyder]]. The 56 sponsors include many top companies in the biotech and pharmaceutical industry.<ref>{{cite web|title=LSRF General Information and Sponsors |accessdate=25 May 2013 |url=http://www.lsrf.org/pages/geninfo.htm |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130524052114/http://www.lsrf.org/pages/geninfo.htm |archivedate=24 May 2013 |df= }}</ref> In 2012, Brown won the [[Albert Lasker Special Achievement Award]] in Medical Science, in part for his initiation and 30-year dedication to LSRF.<ref>{{cite web|title=Albert Lasker Special Achievement Award in Medical Science |url=http://www.laskerfoundation.org/awards/2012_s_accept_brown.htm |date=2012 |accessdate=25 May 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130403063723/http://www.laskerfoundation.org/awards/2012_s_accept_brown.htm |archivedate= 3 April 2013 |df= }}</ref>
==Alumni==
Notable alumni include： *[[Philip Beachy]] of [[Stanford]] *[[Ben Barres]] of [[Stanford]] *[[George M. Church]] of [[Harvard]] *[[Gerald F. Joyce]] of the [[Scripps Research Institute]] *[[Robert Sapolsky]] of [[Stanford]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Life Sciences Research Foundation (LSRF) Alumni |url=http://www.lsrf.org/alumni/alumni83.htm |accessdate=25 May 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103081107/http://www.lsrf.org/alumni/alumni83.htm |archivedate= 3 November 2013 |df= }}</ref>
